{
  "text": "\u2022 The second question relates to their role in assessing the severity of disease, primarily for triaging decisions. For example, whether or not to admit a patient from the emergency room or general ward to the ICU. An example of this use for biomarkers was demonstrated by Giamarellos-Bourboulis et al. [CITATION_1] in 1,156 hospitalized patients, showing that mortality rates were 2.6 times higher in patients presenting with sepsis on the general ward with a PCT concentration >0.12 ng/mL than in those with lower PCT levels. The authors suggested that PCT concentrations could thus be used to help identify which patients may benefit from ICU admission [CITATION_2] .",
